<h1><a class='u' href='#___top' title='click to go to top of document'
name="What_is_CPAN_Search?"
>What is CPAN Search? <img alt='^' src='http://st.pimg.net/tucs/img/up.gif'></a></h1>

<p>CPAN Search is a search engine for the distributions,
modules,
docs,
and ID&#39;s on CPAN.
It was conceived and built by Graham Barr as a way to make things easier to navigate.
Originally named TUCS [ The Ultimate CPAN Search ] it was later named CPAN Search or Search DOT CPAN.</p>

<h1><a class='u' href='#___top' title='click to go to top of document'
name="I&#39;m_having_trouble_connecting_to_search_and_I_think_it_may_be_down,_whom_do_I_contact?"
>I&#39;m having trouble connecting to search and I think it may be down,
whom do I contact? <img alt='^' src='http://st.pimg.net/tucs/img/up.gif'></a></h1>

<p>If you are having technical difficulties with the site itself,
send mail to <i>cpansearch@perl.org</i> and try to be as detailed as possible in your note describing the problem.</p>

<h1><a class='u' href='#___top' title='click to go to top of document'
name="Why_is_&#34;Module_X&#34;_not_listed_in_the_Catalogue?_Where_do_I_send_suggestions/feedback?"
>Why is &#34;Module X&#34; not listed in the Catalogue?
Where do I send suggestions/feedback? <img alt='^' src='http://st.pimg.net/tucs/img/up.gif'></a></h1>

<p>The Catalogue on the front page is based on the Perl 5 Module List and if there is a module you think should be included in a particular category,
you may either use the feedback link on the top of the page or send mail to feedback@search.cpan.org with your suggestions.</p>

<h1><a class='u' href='#___top' title='click to go to top of document'
name="I_have_uploaded_a_distribution_to_CPAN_but_queries_on_search.cpan.org_do_not_find_it."
>I have uploaded a distribution to CPAN but queries on search.cpan.org do not find it. <img alt='^' src='http://st.pimg.net/tucs/img/up.gif'></a></h1>

<ul>
<li>There is a delay between when a distribution is uploaded and when it is indexed,
please try again in a few hours.</li>

<li>search.cpan.org only indexes distributions that unpack to a single top-level directory,
i.e.
a distribution that unpacks into its own directory instead of dumping into the current working directory.
We suggest the use of h2xs -cfn YOUR::MODULE to construct the framework and,
once the module is complete,
using make dist to create the distribution for upload to CPAN.
See the <a href="/perldoc?h2xs" class="podlinkpod"
>h2xs</a>,
<a href="/perldoc?ExtUtil%3A%3AMakeMaker" class="podlinkpod"
>ExtUtil::MakeMaker</a>,
and <a href="/perldoc?perlmodlib" class="podlinkpod"
>perlmodlib</a> documentation for more details.</li>
</ul>

