<h1><a class='u' href='#___top' title='click to go to top of document'
name="Can_I_get_the_results_to_be_output_in_XML_format?"
>Can I get the results to be output in XML format? <img alt='^' src='http://st.pimg.net/tucs/img/up.gif'></a></h1>

<p>Yes,
by adding a &#39;format=xml&#39; in the URL like so: <a href="http://search.cpan.org/search?mode=module&#38;format=xml&#38;query=LWP" class="podlinkurl"
>http://search.cpan.org/search?mode=module&#38;format=xml&#38;query=LWP</a> This feature is NOT supported and it may change at any time so don&#39;t build applications to depend on its continued presence.</p>

<h1><a class='u' href='#___top' title='click to go to top of document'
name="Can_I_get_an_RSS_file_of_the_recent_modules_for_my_news_portal,_etc?"
>Can I get an RSS file of the recent modules for my news portal,
etc? <img alt='^' src='http://st.pimg.net/tucs/img/up.gif'></a></h1>

<p>Yes,
we have an RSS file at <a href="http://search.cpan.org/rss/search.rss" class="podlinkurl"
>http://search.cpan.org/rss/search.rss</a>.
If you use it,
you must also provide a link back to CPAN Search at <a href="http://search.cpan.org/" class="podlinkurl"
>http://search.cpan.org/</a>.
Please send a note to feedback@search.cpan.org to inform us of the URL.</p>

<h1><a class='u' href='#___top' title='click to go to top of document'
name="Is_there_a_API?"
>Is there a API? <img alt='^' src='http://st.pimg.net/tucs/img/up.gif'></a></h1>

<p>Yes,
there are API urls that will return JSON.
Here are some examples</p>

