<h1><a class='u' href='#___top' title='click to go to top of document'
name="Do_you_keep_statistics_on_which_modules_are_most_popular?"
>Do you keep statistics on which modules are most popular? <img alt='^' src='http://st.pimg.net/tucs/img/up.gif'></a></h1>

<p>No. search.cpan.org is only one way to access what is on CPAN. Any statistics gathered by search.cpan.org would not be very representative because we have no way to gather statistics for downloads from all the worldwide CPAN mirrors</p>

<h1><a class='u' href='#___top' title='click to go to top of document'
name="Where_do_the_author&#39;s_pictures_come_from_and_how_do_I_set_mine?"
>Where do the author&#39;s pictures come from and how do I set mine? <img alt='^' src='http://st.pimg.net/tucs/img/up.gif'></a></h1>

<p>They come from the Gravatar associated with that author&#39;s cpan.org email address. To set yours, simply sign up at <a href="http://site.gravatar.com/signup" class="podlinkurl"
>http://site.gravatar.com/signup</a> using your cpan.org address. We cache the gravatars so give it a day or so to catch up.</p>

